Directives are special tokens in the markup that tell the library to 
do something to a DOM element. Common Vue.js directives include:

1. v-bind: Dynamically binds one or more attributes.
2. v-model: Creates a two-way binding on an input, select, or textarea.
3. v-if / v-else-if / v-else: Conditionally renders elements.
4. v-for: Renders a list of items.
5. v-on: Attaches event listeners.
Example:


<div id="app">
  <p v-if="seen">Now you see me</p>
  <button v-on:click="seen = !seen">Toggle</button>
</div>